.SS "void print_level_prefix (\fBlog_level_t\fP level)"

.PP
Print the colored log level to stdout/stderr\&. This is an internal function\&. It prints the log header (e\&.g\&. \fR\fP[INFO]) to \fRstdout\fP (or \fRstderr\fP, if the log level is \fRLOG_ERROR\fP\&.) These headers are colored using ANSI escape codes

.PP
