.SS "void write_log (\fBlog_level_t\fP level, const char * content,  \&.\&.\&.)"

.PP
Print the log content to stdout/stderr\&. This function outputs the log message with the approate header\&. e\&.g\&. [INFO] Hello\&.

.PP
If the log level is \fRLOG_ERROR\fP, the message will be printed to \fRstderr\fP\&. Otherwise the log is printed through \fRstdout\fP\&.

